1
00:00:07,151 --> 00:00:09,867
Today we’re going to go
over the pronunciation

2
00:00:09,867 --> 00:00:12,826
for the idiom ‘to pay
through the nose’.

3
00:00:12,826 --> 00:00:15,627
You might use this phrase when
you are talking about something

4
00:00:15,627 --> 00:00:18,383
that you’ve paid a large
amount of money for.

5
00:00:18,383 --> 00:00:22,399
For example, someone might say, I
love your car and you might say,

6
00:00:22,399 --> 00:00:25,384
Yes, I paid through the nose for it.

7
00:00:25,384 --> 00:00:28,816
Or, for example, I paid through
the nose for my computer

8
00:00:28,816 --> 00:00:31,227
and it broke in the first week.

9
00:00:31,227 --> 00:00:33,937
Another example: I’d like
to live in Manhattan,

10
00:00:33,937 --> 00:00:36,923
but you have to pay through
the nose to live there.

11
00:00:36,948 --> 00:00:41,618
Pay begins with the unvoiced
pp P consonant sound

12
00:00:41,618 --> 00:00:45,280
and is followed by the ‘ay’
as in ‘say’ diphthong.

13
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,671
Pay.

14
00:00:46,671 --> 00:00:47,805
Through.

15
00:00:47,805 --> 00:00:52,052
The TH here is unvoiced
th, th, through.

16
00:00:52,052 --> 00:00:56,588
The R sound is followed by the
‘oo’ as in ‘boo’ vowel sound.

17
00:00:56,588 --> 00:00:57,897
Pay through.

18
00:00:57,897 --> 00:00:59,557
Pay through.

19
00:00:59,582 --> 00:01:00,477
The.

20
00:01:00,477 --> 00:01:07,864
Here, the TH is voiced, and the schwa
sound makes up the rest of the word.

21
00:01:12,451 --> 00:01:16,957
Nose begins with the
N consonant sound,

22
00:01:16,957 --> 00:01:21,840
followed by the ‘oh’ as in
‘no’ diphthong, no-, no-,

23
00:01:21,865 --> 00:01:26,555
and finally, zz, the
voiced Z consonant sound.

24
00:01:26,555 --> 00:01:27,898
Nose.

25
00:01:27,898 --> 00:01:29,504
Pay through the nose.

26
00:01:29,529 --> 00:01:33,103
The two stressed words in
this phrase are pay,

27
00:01:33,103 --> 00:01:38,715
or paid if you are speaking
in the past tense, and nose.

28
00:01:38,715 --> 00:01:41,076
You have to pay through the nose.

